The paper proposes a new probabilistic model for subset selection that is useful for diverse recommendation systems. This falls under the broad category of machine learning and artificial intelligence, which is covered by cs.LG and cs.AI. The paper also discusses efficient sampling procedures and learning quality measures, which are topics related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the application of the proposed model to news article recommendation systems suggests a connection to social and information networks (cs.SI).
